Sentencas: The electrochemistry of oxygen reduction on porous composite electrodes consisting of La((1-x))SrxMnO3-delta (LSM) and Y-stabilised zirconia (YSZ) has been analyzed for better understanding of the mechanism of oxygen reduction and improvement of the cathode's performance.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes

Sentencas: Half cells consisting of YSZ electrolyte pellets and slurry coated cathodes were tested with a three electrodes configuration.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes

Sentencas: The composite cathodes considered in this study have a fixed volume ratio LSM/YSZ equal to 1 and variable apparent Surfaces.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes
Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes

Sentencas: The dependence of electrode resistance on size indicates that the process takes place in the bulk of the cathodes.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes

Sentencas: Part of the impedance data is additionally analyzed by the technique of the Differential Impedance Analysis (DIA), which does not need a preliminary working hypothesis.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes

Sentencas: The application of DIA gives additional information about the dominant phenomena, based on comparative study of the cathode behavior of LSM and of the composite materials.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of oxygen reduction in SOFC composite electrodes
